(41, 8, 2, 40, 14, 14, 14, 'compassion on the multitude', 'Compassion for the Multitude', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' compassion for the multitude. In Mark, he expresses concern for their physical needs, while in Matthew, he is moved with compassion to heal their sick.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 8, 2, 41, 5, 19, 19, NULL, 'Compassion of Jesus', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' compassion in both passages. In Mark 8:2, Jesus expresses compassion for the hungry multitude, while in Mark 5:19, He instructs a healed man to share how He has had compassion on him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
